properties.abstract: This tour will make any biker's heart beat faster: Panoramic views of the Rätikon mountain chain from Alp Valpun, the Stoffenburg single track, the insider's tip in Prättigau.
properties.description:
After Pany we encounter our first rigorous climb.
On a section of the legendary Swiss Bike Masters course the tour follows an alpine road past Bova and continues to Alp Valpun. There we reach the highest point of the tour. The panoramic view of the Rätikon mountain chain is stunning.

From then on it is just one technical treat after another: On an easy single track you now ride westwards towards Stels, always with great views. Then the highlight of the whole tour follows: the steep and technically demanding single track past Stoffenburg to Lunden. 

And in Lunden again a section of the legendary Swiss Bike Masters course is waiting to be mastered. If you want to save yourself the final climb to Pany, take the post bus from Schiers or Küblis (max. 5 bikes per course).
